When an offer is made to a specific person or group of persons, it is
called specific offer. Specific offer can be accepted only by the person or persons
to whom it is made. A general offer is made to public in general and it may be
accepted by any person who fulfils the conditions mentioned in it.
EXAMPLES
a. M makes an offer to N to sell his bicycle for Rs. 800, it is a specific offer. In
this case only N can accept it.
