4. Death or Insanity of Offeror
An offer terminates on death or insanity of the offeror, if the offeree
comes to know about the death or insanity of offeror before his acceptance. If the
offeree does not know about the death or insanity of offeror and gives his
acceptance, it is valid acceptance. It results in a valid contract and legal
representatives of the deceased offeror will be bound by the contract.
