3. Prescribed Manner
Offer And Acceptance
If the offeror prescribes a particular manner of acceptance, the offeree
must accept according to that particular manner. If acceptance is not made
according to the prescribed manner, the offeror may reject it. If no particular
manner is prescribed in the offer then acceptance should be made in a
reasonable manner.
