but does not reply. B sells to C. A has no legal remedy against B.
b. The manager of a railway company received a draft agreement relating to
supply of coal. The manager approved and put the agreement in the drawer
and forgot all about it. Held, there was no contract, as the other party was not
informed. (Brodgen vs. Metropolitan Railway Co.)
5. Express or implied
When an acceptance is given by words spoken or written, it is called
express acceptance. When acceptance is given by conduct or action it is called
implied acceptance. If the offer is made to the public, the contract arises when
any person accepts it by words or conduct.
