2. Defeats Provisions of Law
If the object or consideration of an agreement is of such a nature that if
permitted it would defeat the provisions of any law, then it is considered illegal.
Such objects or considerations may not be directly forbidden by law but they will
indirectly violate law.
EXAMPLE
