QUASI CONTRACT
Quasi contract arises under some special circumstances. It is an
obligation imposed by law upon a person for the benefit of another even in the
absence of a contract. It is based on the principle of equity and justice. It states
that nobody shall be allowed to become rich at the cost of another. Sometimes,
law requires that a particular person must perform some obligations. Such
obligations are called quasi contracts. They are also called constructive
contracts.
