Exemplary damages are awarded to punish the guilty party for the breach
of contract. The breach of contract results in monetary loss to the aggrieved party
and causes disappointment. Exemplary damages have no place in law of
contract and are not recoverable. These are awarded in the following cases:
1. In case of breach of a contract to marry, the amount of damage depends
upon the extent of injury to the feelings of the party.
