Remedies For Breach of Contract
When parties to a contract fix the amount of damages for the breach of
contract at the time of formation of contract, such damages are called liquidated
damages. Where a sum is agreed in the contract to be paid by the defaulting
party in case of breach of contract, the court will allow the reasonable damages
not exceeding the amount already agreed. If the actual loss is more than the
agreed amount, damages will be payable to the agreed amount. (Sec. 74)
EXAMPLE
