a. A agrees to sell his plot to C, who wants to erect a mill. A commits breach.
On the suit of C, A is directed by the court to perform the contract.
b. A agrees to sell B his painting but commits breach. B cannot sue for
damages. A shall be ordered to make specific performance to B.
5. Suit for Injunction
Injunction is an order of a court, restraining a person from doing
something which he promised not to do. It is a mode of securing specific
performance in the negative form. It is a preventive relief. It is a discretionary
remedy of the court. It is appropriate in cases of anticipatory breach of contract.
