Surety's Liability
Extent of Surety's Liability
The liability of surety is co-extensive with that of the principal debtor
unless it is otherwise provided by the contract. The phrase 'co-extensive with that
of principal debtor' shows the quantum of the surety's liability. It means that the
liability of a surety is the same as that of a principal debtor unless there is a
