Termination of Bailment
A contract of bailment terminates under the following circumstances:
1. Expiry of Time
When the contract of bailment is made for a specified period of time, the
bailment terminates after the expiry of that specified time period.
EXAMPLE
A stores B's oranges in the cold storage for a month. After 1 month, the
bailment terminates.
2. Accomplishment of Purpose
If the contract of bailment is made for a specific purpose, the bailment
terminates as soon as the purpose is accomplished.
