b. Agency by Holding Out
The principal is bound by the acts of the agent if, on an earlier occasion,
he made other persons to believe that the person doing some acts on his behalf
is doing with authority. But if an agent has a limited authority, the principal is not
bound for his acts beyond that authority.
EXAMPLE
