accounts of sale and render to P on his demand.
4. Duty to Communicate
It is the duty of an agent, in case of difficulty, to use reasonable diligence
in communicating with his principal and in seeking to obtain his instructions. (Sec
214)
But if it is impossible to get instructions from the principal, the agent can
act on his own in the interests of his principal.
