1. Quiet Possession
161
It is an implied warranty to the buyer that he shall have the possession
and enjoyment of the goods sold to him without disturbance from the seller or
any other person. If the buyer is disturbed in the enjoyment of the goods due to
the seller's defective title, he can claim damages from the seller. (Sec. 14 (b))
