5. Goods to be measured
When there is a contract for the sale of specific goods in a deliverable
state but the seller is bound to weigh, measure, test or do some other act or thing
with reference to the goods for the purpose of ascertaining the price, the property
does not pass until such act is done and the buyer has notice thereof. (Sec 22)
