were destroyed by fire. Held, the loss fell on Z because the ownership had not
transferred to F. (Zagury vs. Furnell)²
6. Unconditional appropriation
When there is a contract for the sale of unascertained or future goods by
description, the property in the goods passes to the buyer when goods of that
description in deliverable state are unconditionally appropriated to the contract,
either by the seller with assent of the buyer or by the buyer with assent of the
seller. (Sec. 23(1))
