2. Mercantile Agent
When a mercantile agent is, with the consent of the owner, in possession
of goods or documents of title to goods, any sale made by him in the ordinary
course of business shall be valid provided the buyer acts in good faith and
without notice that the seller had no authority to sell. (Provisio to Sec 27)
