The buyer is deemed to have accepted the goods in the following
circumstances: (Sec. 42).
a. When he informs the seller that he has accepted the goods.
b. When he does any act, in relation to the goods, which shows that he has
accepted them.
c. When, after the lapse of a reasonable time, he retains the goods without
intimating the seller that he has rejected them.
