a. A sells and delivers wheat to B. B informs A that he has accepted the goods.
b. A buys rice from B and takes delivery from B. A does not reject. It means that
A has accepted the rice after a reasonable time.
16. Rejection of Goods
When goods are delivered to the buyer and he refuses to accept them,
having the right to do so, he is not bound to return them to the seller. He should
only inform the seller about his rejection. (Sec.43)
EXAMPLE
A supplies wrong goods to B. B rejects the goods and does not return.
17. Refusal to take Delivery
When the seller is ready to deliver the goods and requests the buyer to
take delivery, and the buyer does not take delivery of goods within reasonable
time, the buyer is liable to the seller for any loss arising due to the refusal. (Sec.
44)
