Noting
When a note or a bill has been dishonoured by non-acceptance or non-
payment, the holder may cause such dishonour to be noted by a Notary Public
upon the instrument, or upon a paper attached thereto. For this the holder takes
the bill or note to the Notary Public who makes a demand for acceptance or
