Inspection Staff
The Provincial Government is authorized to appoint the Inspector, Chief
inspector and Additional inspectors. Every District Magistrate works as an
Inspector of factory for his district. The Inspector can exercise his powers within
his district. No person can act as Inspector or Chief Inspector if he is or becomes
directly or indirectly interested in a factory or in any process or business carried
on therein or in any patent or machinery connected therewith. The powers of
inspector are as under: (Sec. 10-11)
1. He can enter with assistants any place which is used as a factory or by the
existing circumstances can be deemed to be a factory.
2. He can examine the premises, plant, and of any prescribed registers.
3. He can take on the spot or otherwise such evidence of any person as may be
necessary.
4. He can exercise such other powers as may be necessary for the purposes of
the Act.
