In settling the accounts of a firm after dissolution, the goodwill shall be
included in the assets and it may be sold either separately or along with other
property of the firm. (Sec. 55 (1))
2. Sharing of deficiency
If the assets of a firm are insufficient to pay the debts and liabilities of the
firm, the losses of firm including deficiency of capital shall be paid: (Sec. 48(a))
a. First, out of profits.
b. Next out of capital, and
